09/08/2009
BUCHAREST, Romania -- An explosion in a steel foundry owned by the Russian company Mechel in the town of Targoviste in southern Romania on Saturday (August 8th) injured six people. Two are in serious condition and were taken to a Bucharest hospital, while the remaining four were taken to a local hospital. According to the preliminary information, the explosion was caused by an overload of lime-kiln. (AFP, Bucharest Herald - 08/08/09)
